sections.content:
“discharge” means to cause the discharge of a shot, bullet or other 
missile from a firearm by means of an explosive charge, and includes 
the causing of a bomb or grenade to explode;

(a)  to  sell  or  transfer,  or  keep  or  expose  for  sale  or  transfer,  
a  firearm  in  contravention  of  subsection  9(1)  of  the  
Arms Act 1960 [Act 206];
